New Zealand Beats England 33-22 to Clinch Rugby’s Junior World Title

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-06-26T19:25:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-26/new-zealand-beats-england-33-22-to-clinch-rugby-s-junior-world-title.html
New Zealand  beat  England  33-22 in
the final to win the IRB Junior World Championship rugby title
for the fourth straight time.  The Baby Blacks got tries from Charles Piutau, Ben
Tameifuna and Beauden Barrett in the under-20 event in
Padova,  Italy , today. Gareth Anscombe kicked 18 points.
Christian Wade got two tries and Henry Thomas scored one for
England.  New Zealand is also Women’s Rugby  World Cup  and IRB Sevens
World Series champion. It hosts the men’s World Cup in September
and October.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 